{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB1770", "title": "Arbitration: health care service plans.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Arbitration", "healthcareserviceplans"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Existing law, the Knox-Keene Health Care Service Plan Act of 1975, provides for the licensure and regulation of health care service plans by the Department of Managed Health Care. Existing law provides that a willful violation of provisions regulating health care service plans is a crime. Existing law requires a health care service plan contract that includes terms requiring binding arbitration for dispute settlement to provide a specified disclosure to subscribers or enrollees. Existing law, the California Arbitration Act, provides a statutory framework for the enforcement of contractual arbitration under California law. Existing law establishes standards for arbitration, and requires a court to vacate an arbitration award if it makes certain findings.\n\nThis bill would require the Attorney General to oversee compliance by health care service plans with specified provisions regulating the use of binding arbitration to settle disputes. The bill would authorize the Attorney General to require reports from health care service plans for these purpose."}], "other_titles": [{"note": "", "title": "Arbitration: health care service plans and health insurers."}], "other_identifiers": [{"identifier": "ocd-bill-ca-20252026-ab1770"}], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2026-02-09", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee March 12.", "date": "2026-02-10", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Coms. on HEALTH and JUD.", "date": "2026-02-23", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Coms. on HEALTH and JUD.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "From committee chair, with author's amendments: Amend, and re-refer to Com. on HEALTH. Read second time and amended.", "date": "2026-04-13", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["amendment-introduction", "amendment-passage", "reading-1", "reading-2"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Re-referred to Com. on HEALTH.", "date": "2026-04-14", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on HEALTH.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "Re-referred to Com. on JUD. pursuant to Assembly Rule 96.", "date": "2026-04-16", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on JUD. pursuant to Assembly Rule 96.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "From committee: Do pass and re-refer to Com. on APPR. (Ayes 10. Noes 2.) (April 21). Re-referred to Com. on APPR.", "date": "2026-04-22", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["committee-passage", "committee-passage-favorable", "referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on APPR.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "In committee: Set, first hearing. Referred to APPR. suspense file.", "date": "2026-05-13", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "APPR", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}, {"name": "APPR. suspense file.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "Joint Rule 62(a), file